This paper deals with parameterized complexity classes, which are closely related to computational complexity theory. The paper also mentions the parameterized clique problem, which is a well-known problem in graph theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves concepts related to graphs and polynomials, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of exponential sums and arithmetic formulas also suggests that it could belong to cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
